      • setOnlyPlayer

        public void setOnlyPlayer(boolean onlyPlayer)
        Sets whether this command should only be run by players. If this is set to true, this command will only be runnable by objects implementing Player.

        The default value provided when instantiating this CompositeCommand is false. Therefore, this method should only be used in case you want to explicitly edit the value.
        Parameters:
        onlyPlayer - true if this command should only be run by players.

      • setDescription

        public org.bukkit.command.Command setDescription(String description)
        Sets locale reference to this command's description. It is used to display the help of this command.

        A default value is provided when instantiating this CompositeCommand:
        • "commands." + getLabel() + ".description" if this is a top-level command;
        • "commands." + getParent.getLabel() + getLabel() + ".description" if this is a sub-command.
          Note that it can have up to 20 parent commands' labels being inserted before this sub-command's label. Here are a few examples :
          • /bentobox info : "commands.bentobox.info.description";
          • /bsbadmin range set : "commands.bsbadmin.range.set.description";
          • /mycommand sub1 sub2 sub3 [...] sub22 : "commands.sub3.[...].sub20.sub21.sub22.description".
        This method should therefore only be used in case you want to provide a different value than the default one.
        Overrides:
        setDescription in class org.bukkit.command.Command
        Parameters:
        description - The locale command's description reference to set.
        Returns:
        The instance of this Command.

      • setParametersHelp

        public void setParametersHelp(String parametersHelp)
        Sets locale reference to this command's parameters. It is used to display the help of this command.

        A default value is provided when instantiating this CompositeCommand:
        • "commands." + getLabel() + ".parameters" if this is a top-level command;
        • "commands." + getParent.getLabel() + getLabel() + ".parameters" if this is a sub-command.
          Note that it can have up to 20 parent commands' labels being inserted before this sub-command's label. Here are a few examples :
          • /bentobox info : "commands.bentobox.info.parameters";
          • /bsbadmin range set : "commands.bsbadmin.range.set.parameters";
          • /mycommand sub1 sub2 sub3 [...] sub22 : "commands.sub3.[...].sub20.sub21.sub22.parameters".
        This method should therefore only be used in case you want to provide a different value than the default one.
        Parameters:
        parametersHelp - The locale command's paramaters reference to set.
